cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the need for increased transparency in AI models and services, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on documentation and the challenges faced in creating accurate and useful AI documentation suggest that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely sub-category. The use of AI models and services also falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), while the need for consistent documentation relates to cs.SE (Software Engineering). The potential ethical implications of AI transparency are relevant to cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CR (Computers and Society).
